         <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p>i: Lepcis, the great <supplied reason="subaudible">city</supplied>; Rome loves you.</p>
            <p>ii: To the genius of the colony of Lepcis Magna Crescentina</p></div>
         <div type="translation" source="#tantillo2010" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Leptis Magna ti ama, o Roma! Al Genio della colonia di Leptis Magna, Crescentina fece (?)</p></div>
         <div type="translation" source="#lsa" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Leptis Magna loves you, Roma. Crescentina (set this up) for the Genius of the Colony of Lepcis Magna.</p>
         </div>
         
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>For the acclamation see Robert, loc.cit.</p>
